# Clickable file links

When pointing the user at a local file (PDF, CSV, script output, generated artifact, etc.), **always** use a real markdown link they can open — never a bare path string.

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
web/out/report.csv

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
[report.csv](file:///Users/sidneybrodsky/Dev/pllc-business/new-york-pllc/web/out/report.csv)
```

- Prefer `file://` absolute paths for local artifacts.
- Repo-relative markdown links (`[label](path/from/repo)`) are fine when the client resolves them; still must be markdown links, not plain text.
- Same rule for directories and any path you expect the user to open.
